    "monster": true,
    "notes": "50kg Undead, desert walker, #App: 1d6, Treasure: Large. Claws (2d6+2); armor 4; walks 10m/action; Morale +4. Mummified remains of ancient sorcerers and kings may walk the dead halls of their tombs, forever guarding against interlopers. Undead: immune to poison, disease, and suffocation. Immune to mind-affecting spells. On a successful attack, the mummy exposes the target to a vile, wasting magical disease (9+/2d6/1 day). An infected character cannot heal or enjoy the benefits of magical healing. This is only curable by the Restoration spell. Immune to non-magical weapons, other than fire. Takes double damage from fire-based attacks. A lit torch causes 1d6 damage to mummies.",
